parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Shudder and Second Gear Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch shudder and second gear issues can cause the motorcycle to stall, jerk, or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or near-miss situations.
symptoms: second gear jumping out or slipping

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Violent Shudder When Taking Off in First Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The violent shudder when taking off in first gear can cause loss of control, making it difficult to maneuver the motorcycle, especially when pulling out into traffic, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Violent shudder or vibration when taking off in first gear
clutch feels rough or grabs suddenly
motorcycle hesitates or lurches forward when taking off.
